 Role Description 
 
We are currently seeking a bright and ambitious Corporate Development Associate who will partner with the analyst team and business teams to develop data solutions to achieve our business objectives. We are seeking a self-starter; someone who is excited to dig into the details to understand problems, and exhibits strong communication skills. The successful candidate will demonstrate an ability to influence business owners, support thoughtful decision-making, and adapt to a rapidly evolving environment. This role has high visibility to senior leaders in the company, so absolute professionalism and ability to manage relationships and engage with people of all levels is expected. The position requires a passion for problem solving, an advanced proficiency in Excel and high comfort with exploratory business analysis to synthesize findings into clear, actionable recommendations. In this role, you will make meaningful contributions across a diverse array of projects and will be encouraged to develop a broad skill-set in business strategy, corporate development and operational excellence. 
 
Key Responsibilities 
 
 Supports business requirements by providing end-to-end analysis for ongoing initiatives with respect to data requirements, data flows, data modeling, etc 
 Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders to develop business plans & operational strategies, while identifying operational risk and developing risk mitigation strategies, and designing technical solutions for managing risk 
 Work closely with project managers and team to deliver in-depth analytics and insights using advanced quantitative approaches (e.g. segmentation, profiling, modeling 
 Identify business requirements (independently and in coordination with business partners) and help translate business needs and requirements into functional specifications) 
 Demonstrate ability to work and excel within an environment that is not always black & white; the individual must be comfortable in an environment where answers are not always obvious and sometimes require open-ended analyses + critical thinking to produce a business recommendation 
 Play a key role in developing and supporting strategic and financial planning processes, and evolving the underlying integrated financial models, systems, and tools 
 Prepare high quality presentations and key reporting for review by CEO, CFO, senior leaders and decision makers. 
 Requirements 
 2-4 years of relevant experience in corporate planning, business finance, analytics, investment banking, management consulting, private equity, or related fieldsâ€”including FP&A, M&A, and project management 
 Previous experience supporting an organizationâ€™s financial analysis and forecasting/modeling function 
 Ability to conceptualize and think strategically to identify and methodically resolve potential roadblocks 
 Excellent written and verbal communication skills that are targeted to the appropriate audience (technical and non-technical) at different levels of the organization; ability to support ideas within and among teams 
 Ability to work independently and manage multiple deliverables simultaneously using significant judgement on complex business problem 
 Self-starter who takes initiative and who has exceptional time management skills. 
 
